<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-05-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                    <head>No. 467.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Manning</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-05-11"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 11,
                            1887</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Reports concerning executions at Nogales have been most conflicting since 6th
                        instant. Your telegram announcing appeal is just received with satisfaction.
                        This Government would view with deep regret the imposition of a penalty so
                        extreme, and you are instructed to say that a mitigation would be regarded
                        by us with favor.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>